sury bills and natural resource stocks this was similar to brownes strategy of  of a portfolio in bonds stocks cash and gold with annual rebalancing brownes strategy was portrayed as a failsafe investment strategy and was outlined in his  book failsafe investing the permanent portfolio mutual fund however is more complex than brownes original concept and has six asset categories the fund aims to invest in a fixed percentage of uncorrelated asset categories to minimize risk in changing economic climates these include  in government bonds  in gold and silver bullion  in growth stocks  in cash and swiss francs and  in energy mining and real estate stocks the funds concept is to preserve capital and provide low risk growth through diversification from  through  the funds assets under management aum were less than  million but they grew to  billion in   billion in  and  billion in  as of  the fund had  billion in assets under management with  invested in gold bullion and a relatively high  annual management fee in the s the fund had poor shareholder retention as it badly trailed most stock funds however between feb   and february   the fund averaged an  percent annualized return in comparison to a  percent annualized return for the sp  index when the sp  index dropped  in the financial crisis of  the permanent portfolio fund lost  however from its  inception through  the fund had average annual gains of  in comparison to the sp  stock indexs  average annual gain over the same period the  book the permanent portfolio harry brownes longterm investment strategy discusses the funds benefits and limitations the authors say that the fund managers investment decisions and the costs associated with an actively managed mutual fund are a downside when compared to an index fund but points out that the funds management fee of  per year is below the mutual fund average according to a  article in kiplingers personal finance magazine the fund has delivered on its goal of long term stability with occasional market beating returns  aggressive growth portfolioedit the aggressive growth portfolio pagrx is described as a diversified multicap core us equity fund with the goal of long term appreciation in  it had  million in assets under management and consisted of large and midsized companies in the ten years prior to march  it ranked  amongst  other diversified mutual funds and had a stock management turnover rate of  during that period it never had a negative year and its average annual gain was  better than the sp  index in  its annual management fee was  otheredit the company also offers a shortterm treasury portfolio prtbx which it describes as a shortterm us treasury bonds fund the firms versatile bond portfolio prvbx is said to invest  or more of its net assets in bonds see alsoedit failsafe investing referencesedit  unknown author july   market chatter midnight trader   a b c d e f g h i j k unknown author about us permanent portfolio family of funds retrieved jan     a b c d kosnett jeffrey may  a gold bug gets it right kiplingers   a b c zweig jason september   unlikely superstar how a forgotten fund got hot in a hurry the wall street journal retrieved january     unknown author feb   stocks slip again as slowrecovery fears multiply bloomberg news   a b rowland craig lawson jm  the permanent portfolio harry brownes longterm investment strategy hoboken new jersey wiley global finance pp  to    a b c connell shaun march   how to build an automatic failproof portfolio gurufocus   tazner andrew dec  best funds for rough seas kiplingers   grant tim february   spinning cash into gold pittsburg postgazette   roy debarati august   gold forecasters splitting opinions bloomberg news   unknown author september  simple vs complicated portfolios consumer reports money adviser   nguyen phamduy may   europes crisis lifts gold to near record silver jumps bloomberg news   connell shaun march   permanent portfolio etf gurufocus   prince michael june  kiplinger